The knockback from the enchanter PBAOES's is<br>
a perceived effect in my opinion.  If the mob<br>
that is being stunned happened to have been<br>
in movement mode at the time that it was success-<br>
fully stunned, our refresh will position the mob<br>
instantly at the spot to which it had been moving<br>
without rendering the anim from point to point,<br>
and thus it appears that the mob was knocked<br>
back, when in reality, it was already there, and<br>
our refresh hadn't caught up with it yet.  Similar<br>
to rooting a fleeing mob and seeing it &quot;hop&quot; to<br>
its actual location.  Just my thoughts on it since<br>
the spdat doesn't jive with the idea of a knock-<br>
back property, and yet the mobs DO appear to<br>
move on occasion.<br>
<br>
