That said, the displacement effect from enchanter stuns is negligible, you will see more movement due to damage AE's and stun-resisted mobs movement.<br>
<br>
It is still a good idea to face into a corner to keep them as tightly packed as possible, but the stunner can be standing a step or two back... that allows stunning all the targets and mashing them into the corner, while also not having any of them in a position to backstab the enchanter if it is done right.<br>
<br>
Placement gets more and more critical as you add more targets. If doing large volume AE's, its likely you will gather up mobs in more than one pull, keeping the first (and second etc) group of targets stunned while you wait for the rest to arrive. While the enchanter is keeping them stunned, we (wizards, or other AE damage casters) can help by using AE's WITH knockback, like Thunderclap, to push any outlying mobs into the corner with the rest of the pack, reducing the chance any will drift out of the AE stun or DD areas once you have enough to be worth burning down.<br>
<br>
Even with the best enchanters, I would say you need 2 if you plan on killing more than 15 at a time, or the lack of overlap, the law of averages, and resist rates to the stuns will kill the enchanter.<br>
<br>
